{
  "date": "2026-02-07",
  "title": "Become Still Enough",
  "scriptures": [
    {
      "ref": "Psalm 46:10",
      "text": "Be still, and know that I am God:"
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "key": "read_this_out_loud",
      "label": "Read This Out Loud",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Stillness is not emptiness."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It is a place where I remember who God is."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I do not need to carry everything at full speed."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I can become still enough to know again."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_devotional",
      "label": "The Devotional",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Noise can make a person feel productive while leaving them inwardly thin."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Motion can create the illusion of control."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But stillness exposes what hurry often hides."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Psalm 46 does not tell us to become passive."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It tells us to stop long enough to know."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "To remember."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "To see God as God again."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "That kind of stillness is not laziness."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It is trust made quiet."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_shift",
      "label": "The Shift",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You do not become strong only by pushing harder."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Sometimes you become clear by becoming still."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Silence can reveal.",
            "Slowness can restore.",
            "Attention can re-order the soul."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Stillness makes room for remembrance."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_truth",
      "label": "The Truth",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "If you never stop, you may forget what only quiet can teach."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "God is not made more real by your speed."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He is simply remembered more clearly when you stop running long enough to notice Him."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "reflection",
      "label": "Reflection",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "What has my pace been doing to my attention?",
            "Where do I resist stillness the most?",
            "What might I remember about God if I gave Him unhurried space today?"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "declaration",
      "label": "Declaration",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I do not need noise to feel steady."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I will slow down enough to remember who God is."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I will become still enough to know again."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "action_step",
      "label": "Action Step",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Set aside a small pocket of quiet today."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Put the phone down.",
            "Sit without rushing.",
            "Read the verse slowly.",
            "Stay there longer than feels convenient."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Let stillness do its work."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "one_sentence_to_carry",
      "label": "One Sentence to Carry",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "text": "Stillness helps me remember what hurry makes me forget."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "__insert_block_header": "2026-02-07_psalm-46-10_become-still-enough|"
}
